  "body": "When you have done `max approve` and call `increaseAllowance` with any amount then it is overflowing because the way contract code is written - \r\n\r\n```\r\n  function increaseAllowance(address spender, uint256 addedValue) public virtual returns (bool) {\r\n        address owner = _msgSender();\r\n        _approve(owner, spender, allowance(owner, spender) + addedValue);\r\n        return true;\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nhere we are adding the value with the previous allowance and since previous allowance was already max uint256, its overflowing. \r\n\r\n**üíª Environment**\r\nI am using hardhat with solidity upgradable contracts npm version -  4.8.0\r\n\r\nhere is the link for the bug in the code - https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/a4596cab053d46e0bf2957e2ed490cb3921539ee/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol#L179\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\n## Steps - \r\n\r\n1. approve with max uint256\r\n2. call increaseAllowance with any value\r\n\r\n**üî¢ Code to reproduce bug**\r\n\r\n```\r\n  // approve max amount\r\n  const amount = ethers.constants.MaxUint256;\r\n  const tx = nativeToken.connect(payload.signer2).approve(payload.deployer.address, amount);\r\n\r\n // increase allowance\r\n\r\n const amount = 100; \r\nconst tx = nativeToken.connect(payload.signer2).increaseAllowance(\r\n    payload.deployer.address, amount\r\n);\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
